ManSection.Description:
Given that variety is a complex projective space with Coxring S and M a f. p. graded S-module, this method computes a
function f \colon \mathbb{N}_{\geq 0} \to \mathbb{N}_{\geq 0} such that f \left( n \right) =
dim \left( H^0 \left( X_\Sigma, \widetilde{M} \left( n \right) \right) \right). This function is returned.
